  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What is the CSS Box Model?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Every HTML element is represented as a box. The CSS box model defines how the size and spacing of elements are calculated."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Box Model Structure"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Content** – The actual content (text, image)",
        "**Padding** – Space inside the element",
        "**Border** – Surrounds padding and content",
        "**Margin** – Space outside the element"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Example"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "css",
      "value": "div {\n  width: 200px;\n  padding: 20px;\n  border: 5px solid black;\n  margin: 10px;\n}"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Total Width Calculation"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Total Width = Content + Padding + Border + Margin"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "text",
      "value": "200px (content)\n+ 40px (padding)\n+ 10px (border)\n+ 20px (margin)\n= 270px total"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Box Sizing"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "The box-sizing property controls how width and height are calculated."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "css",
      "value": "div {\n  box-sizing: border-box;\n}"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Box-Sizing Types"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "value": {
        "headers": ["Value", "Description"],
        "rows": [
          ["content-box", "Default (padding & border added)"],
          ["border-box", "Includes padding & border in width"]
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Visual Understanding"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Think of the box model as layers: content at the center, surrounded by padding, then border, and finally margin."
    },
